---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CalibrationFigure from '../components/CalibrationFigure.astro';
import Schema from '../components/Schema.astro';
import { SITE, personSchema } from '../site';
import publishedPW from '../assets/images/about/published-practical-wireless.jpg';
import publishedMetrology from '../assets/images/about/published-metrology.jpg';

const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="David Southworth (D2): over forty years in temperature metrology, technical writing, AI tools, web and mobile work, photography and reflective practice."
>
  <Schema slot="head" schema={personSchema(Astro.site)} />
  <article class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-12">
    <p class="label-mark">About</p>
    <h1 class="mt-3">David Southworth</h1>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg text-[var(--fg-soft)]">
      I make digital things and write about them, with a long background in precision measurement
      and a habit of paying close attention.
    </p>

    <div class="prose-cal mt-10 max-w-[var(--container-prose)]">
      <p>
        My working life has centred on temperature metrology, over forty years of calibration,
        training, technical writing and international project work. That background shapes how I
        approach everything else: a stated figure is only meaningful once you understand the
        conditions behind it, and the same is true of most claims.
      </p>

      <h2>Precision and presence</h2>
      <p>
        Precision is not coldness. The care it takes to make a measurement you can defend is the
        same care that good writing or a calm interface asks for.
      </p>

      <div class="not-prose my-8">
        <CalibrationFigure />
      </div>

      <h2>How I work</h2>
      <p>
        I build websites, web apps and tools, I write technical and reflective pieces, and I help
        people get to grips with AI and digital tools through training. I use AI to assist with
        structure and expression in my professional writing; the ideas remain my own, and for
        poetry I use only my own words. I work plainly, say what I can stand behind, and leave out
        what I cannot.
      </p>
      <p>
        A privacy-first instinct runs through the work. Where something does not need to collect
        data, it does not. Both FeelingVault and Between the Waves are built on that principle.
      </p>

      <h2>Background, in brief</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>Over forty years in temperature metrology: calibration, ITS-90, measurement uncertainty.</li>
        <li>Technical writing and plain-English communication for specialist audiences.</li>
        <li>AI and IT training for individuals and small businesses.</li>
        <li>Web and mobile development, including a shipped iOS app.</li>
        <li>Counselling training, and the value of listening deeply.</li>
        <li>Photography, poetry, journaling and parkrun.</li>
        <li>UK-based, working locally and remotely.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        If any of this connects with something you are working on, see the
        <a href={`${base}/projects/`}>projects</a> or <a href={`${base}/contact/`}>get in touch</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Published work</h2>
      <p>
        Articles on temperature measurement, calibration and metrology published in
        <em>Practical Wireless</em>, <em>Cal Lab</em> and the instrumentation and measurement trade press.
      </p>
      <div class="not-prose mt-5 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <Image
          src={publishedPW}
          alt="Practical Wireless magazine, featuring an article by David Southworth"
          widths={[400, 800]}
          sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 360px"
          class="w-full rounded-xl"
          data-reveal="zoom"
        />
        <Image
          src={publishedMetrology}
          alt="Cal Lab, MEPCA and Instrumentation Monthly magazines featuring articles by David Southworth"
          widths={[400, 800]}
          sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 360px"
          class="w-full rounded-xl"
          data-reveal="zoom"
          style="--reveal-delay: 90ms"
        />
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="label-mark mt-10">
      <a href={`mailto:${SITE.email}`} class="hover:text-[var(--accent)]">{SITE.email}</a>
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
